---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.astro'
import '../styles/global.css'
---

<Layout title='About'>
  <div id='image-container' data-dark-section class='relative block w-full max-h-[500px] overflow-hidden'>
    <img src='/images/about-page-cover.jpg' alt='About page Cover Image' class='w-full h-auto object-cover' />
    <div
      id='overlay'
      class='absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full items-center flex justify-center bg-black/80'
    >
      <h1 class='items-center font-bold text-4xl text-slate-300'>ABOUT</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section id='about-content' class='md:flex w-full px-4 lg:px-12 py-12'>
    <div id='about-illustration' class='md:w-1/2 my-8 md:my-0 flex items-center justify-center'>
      <img src='/images/arun.jpg' alt='About page illustration' class="w-full max-w-[300px] h-auto aspect-square object-cover rounded-full shadow border-4 border-gray-100"/>
    </div>
    <div class="md:w-1/2 md:my-auto">
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-bold text-center text-slate-700'>Who I am ?</h2>
      <p class="my-4 md:mb-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        I'm Arun, a writer, editor, researcher, and actor based in Bengaluru,
        India. My background is in the social sciences: I hold a BA in Social
        Sciences and Humanities and an MSc in Applied Linguistics, and for the
        past five years I've been working as a freelancer, primarily in the
        education sector and academia. In my work and in my life, I try to put
        the journey before the destination, focusing on long-term growth rather
        than short-term gratification. 
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed"> As a writing coach, I invite you to look
        closely at your own life and tell your own stories in your own words,
        without relying on anyone else to do it for youâ€”not even AI. If you'd
        like to see more of what I do, you can find me on Instagram, Substack,
        and LinkedIn. For a detailed look at my experience and qualifications,
        you can also browse my CV.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
